---
import DeepDiveLayout from '../../../features/engine/deep/DeepDiveLayout.astro';
---

<DeepDiveLayout
  title="Nodes All The Way Down"
  subtitle="Unified vocabulary — leafs AND parents predicted by the same model."
  notebooks="NB-11, NB-13, NB-17, NB-21, NB-22"
  prevSlug="data-quality"
  prevTitle="Data Quality Odyssey"
  nextSlug="residual-engineering"
  nextTitle="Two Parameters, +22.7pp"
>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>The Vocabulary Problem</h2>
    <p>
      A naive GRU predicts from a flat list of 920 leaf nodes. But execution traces
      contain more than leaf nodes: they contain <em>parent nodes</em> — named sequences
      of leaf nodes that recur across workflows. Ignoring parent nodes means the model
      never learns to predict "I need a database operation" before predicting the
      specific leaf node.
    </p>
    <p>
      Five notebooks trace the discovery that leaf nodes and parent nodes must share
      a single vocabulary, and the consequences of that decision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="vocab-evolution reveal-on-scroll">
    <div class="vocab-step">
      <span class="vocab-label">NB-11</span>
      <div class="vocab-box">
        <span class="vocab-name">Parent-as-Terminal</span>
        <span class="vocab-detail">918 leaf nodes + 326 parent nodes = 1,244 nodes</span>
        <span class="vocab-result">Parent node Hit@1: 0% (bug in predictNext)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vocab-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
        <path d="M12 5v14m0 0l-5-5m5 5l5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <div class="vocab-step">
      <span class="vocab-label">NB-13</span>
      <div class="vocab-box">
        <span class="vocab-name">Canon + FQDN fix</span>
        <span class="vocab-detail">920 leaf nodes + 245 parent nodes = 1,165 nodes</span>
        <span class="vocab-result vocab-result-good">Parent node Hit@1: 41.6% (after bug fix)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vocab-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
        <path d="M12 5v14m0 0l-5-5m5 5l5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <div class="vocab-step">
      <span class="vocab-label">NB-21</span>
      <div class="vocab-box">
        <span class="vocab-name">Frequency capping (MAX=30, FPS)</span>
        <span class="vocab-detail">2,584 → 1,769 training examples</span>
        <span class="vocab-result vocab-result-good">Parent node Hit@1: 82.3%</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <figure class="cinema reveal-on-scroll">
    <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/11-cap-target-distribution.png"
         alt="Parent node target distribution: examples per parent node, log-scale with cumulative coverage" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption><strong>NB-11 · Parent node distribution.</strong> db:postgresQuery dominates with 952 traces. 47% of parent nodes have exactly 1 example — extreme imbalance that makes direct classification hard.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure class="cinema reveal-on-scroll">
    <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/13-argmax-distribution.png"
         alt="Argmax landing: 40.4% of model predictions land on parent nodes; histogram of correct rank distribution with median=34" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption><strong>NB-13 · Argmax landing.</strong> 40.4% of model predictions land on parent nodes. Median correct rank = 34 without unified vocabulary.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>The Canonicalization Breakthrough</h2>
    <p>
      The softmax had a hidden enemy: 28 duplicate leaf-node groups, each generating
      a separate parent node entry. A parent node named <code>std:cap_rename</code>
      and another named <code>code:cap_rename</code> were the same logical operation
      split across two vocabulary slots.
    </p>
    <p>
      Canonicalization at training time — without touching the database —
      collapsed 71 duplicate parent nodes to 240 canonical entries. The softmax signal
      concentrated. Parent node Hit@1 jumped from 40.6% to 66.3%, a +25.7pp gain from
      deduplication alone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="insight-box reveal-on-scroll">
    <span class="insight-label">Key insight</span>
    <blockquote class="insight-quote">
      Do not merge duplicates in the database. Canonicalize at training time.
      The database stores truth; the model trains on a view.
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <div class="cinema-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/11-embedding-space-tool-vs-cap.png"
           alt="Embedding space: leaf node vs parent node similarity distributions, per-dim alignment" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-11 · Embedding alignment.</strong> Leaf nodes and parent nodes share embedding space with corr=0.98+. They are geometrically compatible.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/11-cap-ambiguity.png"
           alt="Parent node ambiguity: parent nodes per leaf-node set and cosine similarity for ambiguous pairs" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-11 · Parent node ambiguity.</strong> 36 ambiguous leaf-node sets. 100% of pairs sim > 0.95 — true duplicates that confuse the softmax.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <section class="deep-section">
    <h2>Frequency Capping with FPS</h2>
    <p>
      Some parent nodes dominate the training set: <code>std:psql_query</code>
      appears in thousands of traces. Without capping, the model learns to predict
      the most common leaf nodes regardless of context.
    </p>
    <p>
      NB-21 evaluated two capping strategies: random subsampling versus
      Farthest Point Sampling (FPS). FPS selects the most diverse subset by
      maximizing distance in intent embedding space, producing a training set
      with mean pairwise similarity 0.62 vs 0.68 for random — better coverage
      of the intent distribution with the same budget.
    </p>
    <p>
      NB-22 revealed the cost: <code>MAX_PER_CAP=30</code> raises parent node Hit@1 to 82.3%
      but drops leaf node Hit@1 from 49.3% to 37.2%. The capping was too aggressive.
      The search for the right cap value continues.
    </p>
  </section>

  <figure class="cinema reveal-on-scroll">
    <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/21-frequency-capping.png"
         alt="Lorenz curve showing Gini coefficient drop from 0.754 to 0.544 after frequency capping; top-10 parent nodes before and after MAX=30 cap" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption><strong>NB-21 · Gini coefficient.</strong> Frequency capping reduces imbalance from 0.754 to 0.544. FPS maintains intent coverage.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure class="cinema reveal-on-scroll">
    <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/22-vocab-composition.png"
         alt="Horizontal stacked bar showing vocab composition: 920 leaf nodes, 245 parent nodes, 40 canonical duplicates, 24 genuinely missing, 20 test/fake" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption><strong>NB-22 · Vocab composition.</strong> 1,165 active nodes. 84 excluded — 40 canonical duplicates, 24 genuinely missing, 20 test/fake.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="cinema-grid reveal-on-scroll">
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/17-vocab-sizes.png"
           alt="Vocabulary sizes across 5 filter scenarios from 920 leaf-nodes-only to 1257 all-parent-nodes" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-17 · Vocab sizes.</strong> Unique+≥2 examples (1,038 nodes) is the recommended configuration — best coverage without noise.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="cinema cinema-compact">
      <img src="/images/engine/deep/node-hierarchy/tsne-by-capability.png"
           alt="t-SNE projection colored by parent node after SHGAT enrichment" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption><strong>NB-10 · t-SNE by parent node.</strong> SHGAT-enriched embeddings cluster by parent node. Leaf nodes that co-execute share embedding neighborhoods.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

</DeepDiveLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Vocab evolution diagram ────────────── */

  .vocab-evolution {
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 32px 48px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .vocab-step {
    width: 100%;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .vocab-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--e-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--e-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--e-cinema-border);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 4px 8px;
  }

  .vocab-box {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    background: var(--e-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--e-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .vocab-name {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--e-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .vocab-detail {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .vocab-result {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--e-text-dim);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .vocab-result-good {
    color: #16a34a;
  }

  .vocab-arrow {
    color: var(--e-border);
    padding: 4px 0;
    align-self: center;
    margin-left: 80px;
  }

  /* ── Insight box ────────────────────────── */

  .insight-box {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 16px;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  .insight-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--e-accent);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .insight-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--e-accent);
    background: var(--e-accent-glow);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--e-text-secondary);
  }

  .deep-section code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.88em;
    background: var(--e-surface);
    padding: 2px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--e-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .vocab-evolution,
    .insight-box {
      padding-inline: 20px;
    }

    .vocab-step {
      grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
    }
  }
</style>
